{
  "texts": [
    "Here, \"reasoning\" refers to the \"thinking procedure\" for how to recommend suitable items to users, and decide the details of the subsequent action.",
    "Meanwhile, \"action\" entails executing the directives derived from reasoning, making \"observations,\" and yielding the corresponding outcome.",
    "At each step 𝑡, the LLM-driven surrogate user û receives an observation 𝑜 𝑡 -1 from the last step and derives a thought 𝑔 𝑡 to take an action A 𝑡 following some policy 𝜋 (𝑔 𝑡, A 𝑡 |𝑐 𝑡), where 𝜋 could be implemented by any LLMs, specifically ChatGPT, in our ToolRec, and𝑐 𝑡 = (𝑜 0, 𝑔 1, A 1, 𝑜 1,..., 𝑔 𝑡 -1, A 𝑡 -1, 𝑜 𝑡 -1)is the context to the û.",
    "The primary objective is to deduce the policy and mapping 𝑐 𝑡 → (𝑔 𝑡, A 𝑡).",
    "As shown in the left of Figure 1, within the context 𝑐 𝑡, û observes a discrepancy in the movie actors between the retrieved movies and the user's previous movies."
  ]
}